        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <p>Revenza can be installed directly from your platform's app store or via a JavaScript snippet. No coding is required for basic setup.</p>

        <h3>Shopify</h3>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">Open the <strong>Shopify App Store</strong> and search for <strong>Revenza Upsell Addons</strong>.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">Click <strong>Add app</strong> and approve the requested permissions (read products, write cart attributes).</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">You will be redirected to the Revenza dashboard. Your store is now connected.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body">Enable the addons you want from the <strong>Modules</strong> tab and publish.</div></div>
        </div>

        <h3>WooCommerce</h3>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">Download the Revenza plugin zip from your account dashboard.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">In WordPress, go to <strong>Plugins → Add New → Upload Plugin</strong> and upload the zip.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">Activate the plugin and paste your <strong>API key</strong> from the Revenza dashboard.</div></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Custom / headless stores</h3>
        <p>Add the Revenza script tag to your site's <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>. Replace <code>YOUR_STORE_ID</code> with the ID found in your dashboard settings.</p>
        <div style="background:var(--color-background-secondary);border-radius:var(--border-radius-md);padding:12px 16px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--color-text-primary);border:0.5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary);margin-bottom:1rem;">
