      <!-- UPSELL POPUP -->
      <div id="section-upsell-popup" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="badge badge-purple">Addon</div>
        <h2>Upsell popups</h2>
        <p>The upsell popup addon displays a modal overlay with a product offer at a key moment in the buying journey — typically after a customer adds a product to their cart.</p>

        <h3>How it works</h3>
        <p>When a trigger condition is met (e.g. a specific product is added to cart), Revenza renders a lightbox popup featuring a recommended product, a short description, optional discount, and an add-to-cart button. The customer can accept or dismiss the offer without leaving the current page.</p>

        <h3>Configuration options</h3>
        <table class="kb-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Trigger product</td><td>The product that activates the popup when added to cart</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Offer product</td><td>The product shown in the popup</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Discount type</td><td>Fixed amount, percentage, or free shipping</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Countdown timer</td><td>Optional urgency timer (e.g. "Offer expires in 5:00")</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Display frequency</td><td>Show once per session, once per day, or always</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Best practices</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Match the offer product to the trigger product's category for highest relevance.</li>
          <li>Keep popup copy concise — one headline, one sentence of value, one CTA.</li>
          <li>Discounts of 10–20% outperform higher discounts in most verticals.</li>
          <li>Limit popup frequency to once per session to avoid shopper fatigue.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- PRODUCT BUNDLES -->
      <div id="section-bundle" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="badge badge-teal">Addon</div>
        <h2>Product bundles</h2>
        <p>The bundle addon lets you group two or more products and offer them at a combined discount. Bundles appear on product pages, collection pages, or in a dedicated bundle landing page.</p>

        <h3>Bundle types</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Fixed bundle</strong> — a pre-set group of products sold together at a set price.</li>
          <li><strong>Mix-and-match bundle</strong> — the customer picks from a defined product list to build their own bundle.</li>
          <li><strong>Volume discount</strong> — buy 2 get 10% off, buy 3 get 20% off, etc.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Setting up a bundle</h3>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body">Go to <strong>Modules → Product Bundles → Create bundle</strong>.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body">Choose a bundle type and add 2–6 products.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body">Set a bundle discount (fixed price or percentage off total).</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body">Choose where the bundle widget appears: product page, collection page, or both.</div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-body">Save and publish.</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CROSS-SELL -->
      <div id="section-cross-sell" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="badge badge-amber">Addon</div>
        <h2>Cross-sell widget</h2>
        <p>The cross-sell widget renders an inline row of product recommendations directly below the cart line items. Unlike popups, it never interrupts the buyer — it sits passively in the cart sidebar or cart page.</p>

        <h3>Recommendation logic</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Manual rules</strong> — you define which products appear for each cart item.</li>
          <li><strong>Automatic (AI)</strong> — Revenza analyzes past order data to suggest frequently bought together products.</li>
          <li><strong>Collection-based</strong> — recommends from the same collection as the cart item.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Display settings</h3>
        <table class="kb-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Options</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Max products shown</td><td>1–6 tiles</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Widget title</td><td>Custom text (e.g. "You might also like")</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Show price</td><td>Yes / No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Show discount badge</td><td>Yes / No</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Layout</td><td>Horizontal scroll or grid</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- POST-PURCHASE -->
      <div id="section-post-purchase" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="badge badge-purple">Addon</div>
        <h2>Post-purchase offer</h2>
        <p>The post-purchase offer displays a one-click upsell page immediately after the customer completes checkout — before they reach the order confirmation screen. The customer can add the offer to their order with a single click, without re-entering payment details.</p>

        <h3>Why post-purchase?</h3>
        <p>Purchase intent is at its highest right after checkout. The customer has already committed and their payment method is loaded. Post-purchase offers convert at 2–5× the rate of pre-checkout offers for many merchants.</p>

        <h3>Key settings</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Offer product</strong> — the product shown on the post-purchase page.</li>
          <li><strong>Exclusive discount</strong> — flag the offer as only available on this page.</li>
          <li><strong>Accept / Decline copy</strong> — customize button labels.</li>
          <li><strong>Order conditions</strong> — only show if the order total exceeds a minimum, or contains a specific product.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Platform notes</h3>
        <p>Post-purchase upsells require a supported checkout integration. On Shopify, this uses the native post-purchase extension API and does not require any theme edits. On WooCommerce, a redirect is used after the "Thank you" page loads.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- IN-CART UPSELL -->
      <div id="section-cart-upsell" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="badge badge-teal">Addon</div>
        <h2>In-cart upsell</h2>
        <p>The in-cart upsell addon adds product offer tiles inside the cart drawer or cart page — above or below the line items. Offers can include a one-time discount to incentivize adding the item.</p>

        <h3>Placement options</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Above line items (high visibility, lower conversion)</li>
          <li>Below line items (lower friction, higher acceptance)</li>
          <li>Above the checkout button (highest urgency placement)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Offer types</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Single product</strong> — one featured offer with a CTA button.</li>
          <li><strong>Product carousel</strong> — swipeable row of 2–4 offers.</li>
          <li><strong>Progress bar upsell</strong> — "Spend $X more to get free shipping" with a progress indicator.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- TRIGGERS & RULES -->
      <div id="section-triggers" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <h2>Triggers & rules</h2>
        <p>Each addon can be configured to show only when specific conditions are met. This lets you target offers precisely and avoid showing irrelevant upsells.</p>

        <h3>Trigger types</h3>
        <table class="kb-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Trigger</th><th>When it fires</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Add to cart</td><td>A specific product or product from a collection is added to cart</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cart value</td><td>Cart subtotal exceeds or falls below a set amount</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cart item count</td><td>Number of unique items reaches a threshold</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Product page view</td><td>Customer visits a specific product detail page</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Cart open</td><td>The cart drawer or cart page is opened</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Exit intent</td><td>Customer moves cursor toward the browser close/back button</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Combining rules</h3>
        <p>Rules can be combined with AND / OR logic. For example: show the popup when <em>product A is in cart AND cart value is over $50</em>.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- DESIGN -->
      <div id="section-design" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <h2>Design & branding</h2>
        <p>All addons are styled using the Revenza visual editor. Changes apply globally to all addons, or can be overridden per module.</p>

        <h3>Global style settings</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Primary color</strong> — used for CTA buttons and accent elements.</li>
          <li><strong>Font family</strong> — inherit from your store theme or set a custom Google Font.</li>
          <li><strong>Border radius</strong> — controls the roundness of cards, buttons, and modals.</li>
          <li><strong>Button style</strong> — filled, outlined, or ghost.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Custom CSS</h3>
        <p>Advanced users can add custom CSS from <strong>Settings → Custom CSS</strong>. All Revenza elements use the <code>.rvz-</code> class prefix (e.g. <code>.rvz-popup</code>, <code>.rvz-bundle-widget</code>).</p>

        <h3>Dark mode</h3>
        <p>Revenza detects your store's color scheme and applies a dark variant automatically. You can disable this in <strong>Settings → Appearance → Force light mode</strong>.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- ANALYTICS -->
      <div id="section-analytics" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <h2>Analytics</h2>
        <p>The Revenza analytics dashboard shows performance metrics for every addon, updated in real time.</p>

        <h3>Key metrics</h3>
        <table class="kb-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Definition</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Impressions</td><td>Number of times an offer was displayed to a customer</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Accepts</td><td>Number of times the offer product was added to cart</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Conversion rate</td><td>Accepts ÷ Impressions</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Revenue attributed</td><td>Total revenue from accepted offers in the period</td></tr>
            <tr><td>AOV lift</td><td>Difference in average order value between orders with and without upsell acceptance</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Exporting data</h3>
        <p>Go to <strong>Analytics → Export</strong> to download a CSV of all events for a selected date range. Data is also available via the Revenza REST API for custom dashboards.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div id="section-faq" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <h3>Will addons slow down my store?</h3>
        <p>No. The Revenza script is loaded asynchronously and deferred until after the page's critical content has rendered. In most cases, the performance impact is under 20ms.</p>

        <h3>Can I show different offers to different customers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Use trigger rules to target by cart contents, order value, or UTM parameters. Customer segment targeting (based on purchase history) is available on the Scale plan.</p>

        <h3>Do addons work with discount codes?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Revenza discounts stack with existing cart-level discount codes. You can also configure addons to only show when no existing discount code is applied.</p>

        <h3>Is there a limit on how many addons I can run simultaneously?</h3>
        <p>You can run all five addon modules simultaneously. We recommend starting with one or two, measuring performance, and expanding from there.</p>

        <h3>Does Revenza work with headless / custom storefronts?</h3>
        <p>Yes, via the JavaScript SDK and REST API. Full headless documentation is available in the developer docs section of your account dashboard.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING -->
      <div id="section-troubleshoot" class="kb-section" style="display:none;">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

        <h3>Addon is not showing</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Check that the addon is toggled <strong>Live</strong> in the Modules tab.</li>
          <li>Verify that your trigger conditions are met. Use the <strong>Preview</strong> mode to simulate a trigger.</li>
          <li>Clear your browser cache and test in an incognito window.</li>
          <li>On Shopify, ensure the Revenza app embed is enabled in <strong>Online Store → Themes → Customize → App embeds</strong>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Popup appears but add-to-cart doesn't work</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Confirm the offer product is in stock and not a subscription-only product.</li>
          <li>Check for JavaScript conflicts by disabling other apps temporarily.</li>
          <li>Review the browser console for errors and include them when contacting support.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Analytics showing zero impressions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Make sure you have visited the page as a customer (not while logged into the admin).</li>
          <li>Analytics data has a 2-minute processing delay. Refresh after a few minutes.</li>
          <li>Verify the Revenza script tag is loading by checking the Network tab in browser DevTools.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Still stuck?</h3>
        <p>Contact our support team at <span style="color:#534AB7;">support@revenza.io</span> or use live chat inside your dashboard. Include your store URL and a description of the issue.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const pages = ['home','apps','kb','pricing','about','contact'];
  const sections = ['overview','install','quickstart','upsell-popup','bundle','cross-sell','post-purchase','cart-upsell','triggers','design','analytics','faq','troubleshoot'];

  function showPage(page) {
    pages.forEach(p => {
      const el = document.getElementById('page-' + p);
      if (el) el.classList.toggle('active', p === page);
      const nav = document.getElementById('nav-' + p);
      if (nav) nav.classList.toggle('active', p === page);
    });
    const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');
    sidebar.style.display = page === 'kb' ? 'block' : 'none';
    if (page === 'kb') showSection('overview');
  }

  function showSection(sec) {
    sections.forEach(s => {
      const el = document.getElementById('section-' + s);
      if (el) el.style.display = s === sec ? 'block' : 'none';
      const sb = document.getElementById('sb-' + s);
      if (sb) sb.classList.toggle('active', s === sec);
    });
  }

  showSection('overview');
</script>
